,Recommended,425720,22659681,"Posted: 27 April, 2016",all,jaeger,"Cloudlands: VR Minigolf is aiming to be the Virtual Reality minigolf experience. Boasting a solid put mechanic, intuitive room-scale and click-to-teleport locomotion, this game is definitely up to par. I have not tried any user generated content yet, the official course has kept me more than happy. The gameplay feels very realistic, though getting your stroke down can be a bit trying as you don't have the weight of an actual club. This game delivers on the familiarity of minigolf while adding elements only available in a digital format- such as moving blocks, cannons, fans, and other obstacles that would be either impossible or impractical in the real world.Pros:+Great headtracking, room-scale, and click-to-teleport locomotion.+Official course is very well designed and a pleasure to play.+Feels like the real thing.+Pleasing visuals.+Putting is consistent once you get a feel for the motion range.Cons:-Local multiplayer is workable, but a hassle. Not really recommended as a party game since you're going to be constantly having to adjust the straps. God forbid someone is wearing glasses and you have to adjust the lenses too.-My localisation appears to be broken. I get random chinese characters on some menu elements and buttons. This is not a gamebreaking issue though since the menus are intuitive enough to guess and get by.-Would be nice if they could introduce a control mechanic to ghost/materialize your club. Theres been times where I've accidentally hit the ball while I'm just trying to look around.-Casual players can become frustrated at the difficulty of some holes, bringing down the mood of the group. Nobody likes failing infront of their friends. Know the people you're trying to play with.-Lack of weight in the controller makes getting a feel for putting more difficult than in real life."
76561197966573552,Recommended,425720,22294405,"Posted: 7 April, 2016",all,Spock RC,"+ Courses look great, fun to walk through+ Controls are solid, easy to pickup and play+ Putting is acurate, ball seems a bit slow tho+ Enviornmental sounds are great (when music is off)- Music quickly becomes maddenning (you can turn it off)- Textures disapear for no reason- Grass / Leave textures look really fake in VR- Courses are unfair if your trying to get a competitive score- Course design neglates player hovering in air / standing in objectsOverall I think this is a solid putt-putt game, but it's not nearly as engaging as some of the other titles. It probably won't get nearly as much play time on my list. Maybe with more content it will get better.Edit: My intial impression was low because 1) the music put me in a bad mood and 2) I had placed a controller on my desk without turning it off, which meant the grid was up all the time and caused some textures to disappear. This is really the best putt-putt game I've played. As a golfer, this is very realistic, to the extent that I curl up my toes as the ball inches toward the hole. I only wish I could disable the texture disappear ""feature"" that is so distracting."
