,Recommended,425720,22635198,"Posted: 25 April, 2016",all,GrandNoodleLite,"Short Review:If you love Minigolf, you'll love this game. If you hate Minigolf, you'll hate this game. Nuff said...Long Review:Cloidlands: VR Minigolf is as close to playing real Minigolf as you're gonna get (hence the short review).Pros:It's Minigolf in VR.The distance the ball goes relative to the power in your swing feels accurate.Great graphics. The pics on the steam store page accurate.Better than real life Minigolf in the sense that if a ball is close to a wall, you can wack the ball through the wall instead of having to nudge it away.There's local and online multiplayer, a rare feature in VR games. For local multiplayer, you give the headset to someone else when it's their turn, and online multiplayer just works.Nice variety in the holes.Cons:There's only one course of 18 holes (as of the time I'm writing this). Because of this it doesn't take long to go through the entire game and there's very little replayability.No voice chat in online multiplayer. The Vive has a mic, so there's no reason it shouldn't be in there.This isn't the Devs' fault, but it's a bit odd using the Vive controler as a golf club, at least for me. Don't get me wrong, it works. It's just doesn't feel like a golf club, probably because it isn't.In Conclusion:If you love Minigolf, go ahead and buy it. If you hate Minigolf, don't buy it. If you're in the middle, I'd get it on sale. I don't think it's worth the $20 in it's current state (as of the time I'm writing this). If they add more than one course I can see people paying full price for it, but untill then I'd wait till it's on sale for $10 or so."
,Recommended,425720,22992859,"Posted: 14 May, 2016",all,Sexy Boat Captain,"This is a really really good VR version of Mini Golf.  I watched the videos and read the reviews, then decided to try it and it's a great game!  It was way above my expectations.  I've got a 980 TI, a subpar i5 and I've got my Lighthouses way too far apart (close to 20 feet) and I had no stuttering or anything.  The gameplay is actually really fun and a lot of thought and time was obviously put into the courses and the environment.  This isn't a slapped together game, it's pretty polished.  In my opinion, the complaints about the club are more in the nit picking range.  It should probably have an option to ghost the club so you don't accidentally hit the ball, and sometimes the hit registration is a little off if you move the club around too much near the ball (which are easy to avoid once you figure out what causes it), but whether these get fixed or not (Update - It's totally user error, I just played three rounds and never accidentally hit it once, I think it's just that when you start playing, you don't control the club properly), the game is still a great game.  Definitely worth the $20.Updating my review.  Just played multiplayer and it's awesome!  So far this is my favorite Vive game.  If you've ever played mini golf and enjoyed it even a little bit, you'll love this even more because you don't have working cannons in regualr mini golf.  If you're a serious golfer, then you probably won't like this because it's mini golf and I'd guess serious golfers wouldn't like mini golf out of principle.Another thing too, the game actually looks a lot better in VR than it does in the videos."
